questions.text:
What is the output of the following code snippet?

```cpp
int val[4] = {10, 20, 30, 40};
for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
    cout << val[i] << " ";
}
```

Trace the following code. What is the value of `sum`?

```cpp
int arr[3] = {5, 10, 15};
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i < 3; i++) {
    sum += arr[i];
}
```

What is the result of the following 2D array trace?

```cpp
int table[2][3] = {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}};
cout << table[1][0];
```

What is the output of this loop logic?

```cpp
int list[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    list[i] = list[i + 1];
}
cout << list[0] << " " << list[4];
```

What will the following code print?

```cpp
char greeting[10] = "Hi";
greeting[1] = 'o';
cout << greeting;
```

Trace this logic to find the largest value:

```cpp
int nums[4] = {12, 45, 7, 33};
int max = nums[0];
for (int i = 1; i < 4; i++) {
    if (nums[i] > max)
        max = nums[i];
}
cout << max;
```

What is the output of the following code snippet?

```cpp
int matrix[2][2] = {1, 2, 3, 4};
int total = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++)
    total += matrix[i][i];
cout << total;
```
